        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="no"/>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>The principal Act is amended by inserting, after <citation jurisdiction="nz">section <atidlm:link xmlns:atidlm="http://www.arbortext.com/namespace/atidlm" atidlm:key="32905" atidlm:branchLabel="_NOVERSION_" atidlm:name="prov 109" atidlm:xmlId="DLM479855" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:linkcontent>109</atidlm:linkcontent><atidlm:resourcepair atidlm:markupType="extref" atidlm:isIncludeOrRef="1" atidlm:seqNum="33512" atidlm:sourceXmlId="DLM479855" atidlm:targetKey="1578016" atidlm:targetXmlId="DLM305420" atidlm:targetName="prov 109" atidlm:sourceName="DLM479855" atidlm:targetLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM304981.xml" atidlm:sourceLocator="file:///C:/epicuser/Doctypes/NZAct/fragxyxz_DLM57209.xml" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Name" atidlm:value="prov" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Amend" atidlm:value="false" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Element_Context" atidlm:value="/act[1]/body[1]/part[1]/prov[16]" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Element_Type" atidlm:value="prov" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Heading" atidlm:value="New section 109A inserted" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Label" atidlm:value="19" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Legislation_Id" atidlm:value="DLM57202" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Legislation_Number" atidlm:value="21" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Legislation_Title" atidlm:value="Education Amendment Act 2000" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Legislation_Year" atidlm:value="2000" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/><atidlm:metadata atidlm:name="Revision_Number" atidlm:value="" atidlm:locale="xx_XX" atidlm:state="UNCHANGED"/></atidlm:resourcepair></atidlm:link></citation>, the following section:</text>
              <amend>
                <prov id="DLM57259" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">109A</label>
                  <heading xml:lang="en-NZ">Provisions relating to Board with staggered election cycle where commissioner appointed</heading>
                  <prov.body>
                    <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
                      <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                        <text>This section applies if a commissioner has been appointed in place of a Board that has, or had decided to have, a staggered election cycle, and the commissioner has appointed a date under <citation jurisdiction="nz">section 109(5)</citation> for the holding of elections of trustees for a new Board.</text>
                      </para>
                    </subprov>
                    <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
                      <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                        <text>Despite anything in <citation jurisdiction="nz">section 102</citation>, the nomination forms and voting forms for the election must show which nominees are standing only until the next election, and which are standing until the election after the next election.</text>
                      </para>
                    </subprov>
                    <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
                      <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                        <text>Despite anything in <citation jurisdiction="nz">section 102</citation>, trustees who are elected only until the next election go out of office at the close of the day before the day on which the successor takes office following the election.</text>
                      </para>
                    </subprov>
                    <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
                      <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                        <text>If the date that the commissioner has appointed under <citation jurisdiction="nz">section 109(5)</citation> is a date that is within 6 months before the date on which an election is due to be held, the Board does not have to hold an election on that date and this section applies as if that election were not due to be held.</text>
                      </para>
                    </subprov>
                  </prov.body>
                </prov>
              </amend>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
      </prov>
