                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
                  <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                    <text>Unless it was (immediately before the merger took effect) a combined Board established under <citation jurisdiction="nz">section 110</citation>, then, subject to <citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (6)</citation>, the Board of the continuing school must hold elections for a new Board on a day that is not later than 3 months after the day the merger took effect.</text>
                  </para>
                </subprov>
                <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4A</label>
                  <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                    <text>Each Board of the merging schools must be represented on the Board of the continuing school by a co-opted trustee for the balance of that Board's term of office, andâ€”</text>
                    <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                      <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                        <text>the Board of the continuing school must co-opt the trustee within 28 days after notice of the merger is published under <citation jurisdiction="nz">subsection (1)</citation>; and</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                      <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                        <text>each co-opted trustee holds office until the trustees elected at the next election take office, and then the co-opted trustee goes out of office; and</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                    <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                      <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                      <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                        <text><citation jurisdiction="nz">section 94C</citation> (which limits the co-option and appointment of trustees) does not apply while this subsection applies.</text>
                      </para>
                    </label-para>
                  </para>
                </subprov>
              </amend>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
      </prov>
